r) library (v0.1.0), deleting the now-duplicated source and updating imports across the workspace.\n\n## Depends on\n- [goggin-rs-logger#1](https://github.com/joegoggin/goggin-rs-logger/issues/1) — the library extraction, specifically the `v0.1.0` tag.\n\n## Scope\nEach workspace crate gets its own sub-issue. Do them in the listed order so the API side is green before the Leptos and dev-tools sides land.\n\n## Git dependency snippet\n```toml\ngoggin-rs-logger = { git = \"https://github.com/joegoggin/goggin-rs-logger\", tag = \"v0.1.0\", features = [...] }\n```\n\nFeature flag per crate:\n- `api/Cargo.toml` → `features = [\"axum\"]`\n- `web/Cargo.toml` → `features = [\"leptos\"]`\n- `dev-tools/Cargo.toml` → `features = [\"axum\"]`\n\n## Verification\n- `just check` across the workspace passes.\n- All 20 existing logging tests now live in the library (removed from gig-log).\n- Manual smoke test: running the API and the frontend still produces identical verbose/compact log output.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joegoggin/gig-log/issues/207/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joegoggin/gig-log/issues/207/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos/issues/641","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos/issues/641/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos/issues/641/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos/issues/641/events","html_url":"https://github.com/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos/issues/641","id":4248890721,"node_id":"I_kwDOIYu7ec79QO1h","number":641,"title":"`wasm_bindgen` module imports are not hashed inside `.wasm` binary when `LEPTOS_HASH_FILES=true`","user":{"login":"johomo","id":28574850,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI4NTc0ODUw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/28574850?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/johomo","html_url":"https://github.com/johomo","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/johomo/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/johomo/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/johomo/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/johomo/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/johomo/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/johomo/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/johomo/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/johomo/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/johomo/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":5,"created_at":"2026-04-12T16:37:23Z","updated_at":"2026-04-19T21:40:14Z","closed_at":"2026-04-19T21:40:14Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"First off, thanks for all the work on this great framework. As a Rust programmer, it's a real joy to build for the web using Rust and Leptos.\n\nPlease let me know if this is actually a bug with cargo-leptos, or if I should move this issue to a different Leptos repository.\n\n## Issue description\n\nWhen building a Leptos SSR project with `LEPTOS_HASH_FILES=true`, `cargo-leptos` correctly hashes the filenames of the generated assets (JS, WASM, CSS). However, if the project uses `wasm_bindgen` to import a local JavaScript file via `#[wasm_bindgen(module = \"/js/javascript.js\")]`, the resulting `.wasm` binary still contains an internal import reference to the unhashed filename.\n\nThis causes a runtime error in the browser because it tries to fetch the original filename (which doesn't exist) instead of the hashed version.\n\nI am available to provide a minimal reproducible example repository if needed.\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create a JavaScript file to be called from Rust:\n```javascript\n// File ./js/javascript.js\nexport function javascriptFunction(config) {\n    console.log(\"Hello from the brower\");\n    // Parameter `config` is not rellevant.\n}\n```\n\n2. Create a Leptos component that imports this function:\n```rust\n// Rust component\nuse leptos::wasm_bindgen::prelude::*;\n\n#[cfg(feature = \"hydrate\")]\n#[wasm_bindgen(module = \"/js/javascript.js\")]\nextern \"C\" {\n    #[wasm_bindgen(js_name = javascriptFunction)]\n    fn javascript_function(config: JsValue);\n}\n\n// This function cannot be run in server-side (javascript is only available in client-side)\n#[cfg(not(feature = \"hydrate\"))]\nfn javascript_function(_: JsValue) {}\n```\n\n3. Build the project in release mode with hashing enabled:\n```bash\nLEPTOS_HASH_FILES=true cargo leptos build --release\n```\n\n4. Run the application:\n```bash\nLEPTOS_HASH_FILES=true cargo leptos serve --release\n```\n\nThe build completes successfully. The files in `./target/site/pkg` are correctly hashed, including the JS snippet:\n```bash\ntarget/site/pkg\n|- leptos-ssr-template.4ul9fK4Rkx4nbHf8QDA-lg.wasm\n|- leptos-ssr-template_bg.wasm.d.VkYcl6ddV5YtKq5nEt4uNg.ts\n|- leptos-ssr-template.5v77LImhofSXRFXocdUK-w.js\n|- leptos-ssr-template.d.ulmSRV_kktnlipBwbGPZgQ.ts\n|- snippets\n    |- leptos-ssr-template-8d6ff23cd77adfac\n        |- js\n            |- firebase-auth2.kjHXRVq3xc0D_h-X1qQMKQ.js\n```\n\n### Actual behavior\nIf we inspect the `.wasm` file, it still references the original unhashed path:\n```wasm\n// File target/site/pkg/leptos-ssr-app.4ul9fK4Rkx4nbHf8QDA-lg.wasm\n(func $./snippets/leptos-ssr-app-8d6ff23cd77adfac/js/javascript.js.javascriptFunction (;0;) (import \"./snippets/leptos-ssr-app-8d6ff23cd77adfac/js/javascript.js\" \"javascriptFunction\") (param externref))\n```\n\nConsequently, the browser (e.g., Chrome) throws the following exception:\n\n```wasm\n(index):1 Uncaught (in promise) TypeError: WebAssembly.instantiate(): Import #0 \"./snippets/leptos-ssr-app-8d6ff23cd77adfac/js/javascript.js\": module is not an object or function\n```\n\n### Expected behaviour\nThe references inside the `.wasm` file should be updated to match the hashed filenames generated by the build process:\n```wasm\n// File target/site/pkg/leptos-ssr-app.4ul9fK4Rkx4nbHf8QDA-lg.wasm\n(func $./snippets/leptos-ssr-app-8d6ff23cd77adfac/js/javascript.kjHXRVq3xc0D_h-X1qQMKQ.js.javascriptFunction (;0;) (import \"./snippets/leptos-ssr-app-8d6ff23cd77adfac/js/javascript.kjHXRVq3xc0D_h-X1qQMKQ.js\" \"javascriptFunction\") (param externref))\n```\n\n### Environment / versions\nHere is the `Cargo.toml` file. Please note that it may contain more dependencies than are strictly necessary to reproduce this error.\n\n```toml\n// Cargo.toml\n\n[package]\nname = \"leptos-ssr-app\"\nversion = \"0.1.0\"\nedition = \"2021\"\n\n[dependencies]\naxum = { version = \"0.8\", optional = true }\nleptos = \"0.8.17\"\nleptos_router = \"0.8.13\"\nleptos_axum = { version = \"0.8.8\", optional = true }\nleptos_meta = \"0.8.6\"\nconsole_error_panic_hook = { version = \"0.1\", optional = true }\nwasm-bindgen = { version = \"0.2.115\", optional = true }\njs-sys = \"0.3.92\"\nweb-sys = \"0.3.92\"\nwasm-bindgen-futures = \"0.4.65\"\n\n[features]\nhydrate = [\n    \"leptos/hydrate\",\n    \"dep:console_error_panic_hook\",\n    \"dep:wasm-bindgen\",\n]\nssr = [\n    \"dep:tokio\",\n    \"dep:axum\",\n    \"dep:leptos_axum\",\n    \"tokio/rt-multi-thread\",\n    \"leptos/ssr\",\n    \"leptos/nonce\",\n    \"leptos_meta/ssr\",\n    \"leptos_router/ssr\",\n]\n\n[profile.wasm-release]\ninherits = \"release\"\nopt-level = 'z'\nlto = true\ncodegen-units = 1\npanic = \"abort\"\n\n[package.metadata.leptos]\noutput-name = \"leptos-ssr-app\"\nsite-root = \"target/site\"\nsite-pkg-dir = \"pkg\"\ntailwind-input-file = \"style/input.css\"\ntailwind-version = \"v4.2.2\"\nassets-dir = \"public\"\njs-dir = \"js\"\nsite-addr = \"127.0.0.1:3000\"\nreload-port = 3001\nend2end-cmd = \"npx playwright test\"\nend2end-dir = \"end2end\"\nbrowserquery = \"defaults\"\nenv = \"DEV\"\nbin-features = [\"ssr\"]\nbin-default-features = false\nlib-features = [\"hydrate\"]\nlib-default-features = false\nlib-profile-release = \"wasm-release\"\nwatch-additional-files = [\"style\", \"js\", \".env\"]\n```\n\nI am available to provide a minimal reproducible example repository if needed.\n\n## Related issues\nI couldn't find any existing issues (open or closed) that shed light on this particular issue. Issue https://github.com/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos/issues/258 seemed similar at first, but it's unrelated to `wasm_bindgen`. I tried the suggested `frontend-files-content-hashes = true` setting anyway, but it didn't fix the problem.\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos/issues/641/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos/issues/641/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/WorldSEnder/wasm-split-prototype/issues/26","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/WorldSEnder/wasm-split-prototype","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/WorldSEnder/wasm-split-prototype/issues/26/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/WorldSEnder/wasm-split-prototype/issues/26/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/WorldSEnder/wasm-split-prototype/issues/26/events","html_url":"https://github.com/WorldSEnder/wasm-split-prototype/is