onfig, using it as a git repository: https://github.com/cloudflare/workers-rs.git\nError: all authentication attempts failed\n```\n\nEven direct command fails:\n```\n~ % cargo generate --git https://github.com/cloudflare/workers-rs.git\nError: all authentication attempts failed\n```\n\nAfter a some digging (checking configs of git, ssh; testing other repos) and reviewing past issues in cargo-generate, it boils down to a recent change in worker-rs repo, related to submodules, being the cause:\n\nhttps://github.com/cloudflare/workers-rs/blob/7ad71392841a4ed049fbf497e6fdf22e5e6732fb/.gitmodules\n\nThe lines\n```\n\turl = git@github.com:guybedford/wasm-streams.git\n\turl = git@github.com:wasm-bindgen/ts-gen\n```\n\ncauses some resolution issue.\n\n## suggested fix\n\nChanging those lines to \n```\n\turl = https://github.com/guybedford/wasm-streams\n\turl = https://github.com/wasm-bindgen/ts-gen\n```\nfixes the issue.\n\n\nRunning the same command against my change runs fine:\n\n```\ntest % cargo generate https://github.com/jccampagne/workers-rs\n⚠️   Favorite `https://github.com/jccampagne/workers-rs` not found in config, using it as a git repository: https://github.com/jccampagne/workers-rs\n✔ 🤷   Which template should be expanded? · templates/hello-world\n🤷   Project Name: test-hello-world\n🔧   Destination: /private/tmp/test/test-hello-world ...\n🔧   project-name: test-hello-world ...\n🔧   Generating template ...\n✔ 🤷   Enable panic=unwind and abort recovery? · false\n[1/5]   Done: .gitignore\n[2/5]   Done: Cargo.toml\n[3/5]   Done: src/lib.rs\n[4/5]   Done: src\n🔧   Moving generated files into: `/private/tmp/test/test-hello-world`...\n🔧   Initializing a fresh Git repository\n✨   Done! New project created /private/tmp/test/test-hello-world\n```\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cloudflare/workers-rs/issues/989/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cloudflare/workers-rs/issues/989/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/39","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/39/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/39/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/39/events","html_url":"https://github.com/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/39","id":4416897010,"node_id":"I_kwDOSXj0Bc8AAAABB0R_8g","number":39,"title":"Restore secondary UI affordances, semantic HTML attributes, and the missing display font","user":{"login":"KonstantinKo","id":779660,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc3OTY2MA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/779660?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo","html_url":"https://github.com/KonstantinKo","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":6,"created_at":"2026-05-10T21:31:12Z","updated_at":"2026-05-11T15:05:26Z","closed_at":"2026-05-11T15:05:22Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"The post-migration port focused on each screen's primary rendering and dropped a long tail of secondary affordances, fallback variants, semantic attributes, and one external resource. None of these are catastrophic individually but together they erode the feel of the app significantly.\n\n## User-visible symptoms\n\n### Missing buttons / variants\n- Stop button in break mode is always X (full reset). The prior version flipped to a back-arrow (\"undo last session\") icon during break, letting the user decrement their completed-pomodoro count if they realized they hadn't actually finished the focus.\n- Skip button only has two icon variants (cup for focus→break, brain for break→focus). The prior version had a moon glyph for the every-fourth focus→long-break case, and a fallback default forward-arrow.\n- The Calendar's \"Edit Session\" modal is read-only — only shows duration. The prior version had Start Time / End Time / Duration inputs that recalculated each other on change, plus Save and Delete buttons.\n- \"Reset to Defaults\" button in Settings is gone. The Advanced tab still has \"Reset All Data\" but that's destructive; there's no way to just restore default durations / notifications / etc. without manually re-editing each field.\n- Excel export button on the Calendar's Session History card is gone. The Tauri command (`commands::export_sessions_xlsx`) is still wired on the backend but unreachable from the UI.\n- Per-shortcut Clear (×) button in Settings → Shortcuts is missing. Users who bind something accidentally have no way to clear it without overwriting it.\n- Per-shortcut description paragraphs are missing — new users get no context on what each shortcut does.\n- Tag icon picker for new tags only shows 5 emoji options (🧠💪🎯⚡🔥). The prior version had 3 additional Remix Icon options (`ri-brain-line`, `ri-focus-3-line`, `ri-lightbulb-line`) before the emoji set.\n\n### Missing UI metadata / labels\n- The user-avatar dropdown header shows only the name; the prior version had a second-line subtitle (\"Guest Mode\" / \"Signed In\") differentiating auth state.\n- The \"Settings are saved automatically\" persistent footer is gone — replaced only by a transient toast on each change, so users who open Settings without editing see no reassurance.\n- The Today's Development chart card has no legend explaining its colored bars (was: \"Focus sessions\" / \"Break time\" with colored squares).\n- The Tag Usage This Week pie-chart card on the Calendar is entirely absent.\n\n### Lost HTML semantics / accessibility\n- Hover tooltips on icons and buttons (`title=\"...\"` attributes) are mostly gone. Some moved to `aria-label`, which screen-readers still see but sighted hover users don't. (Sidenote: the prior version had a tooltip-out-of-bounds rendering bug — fix that when restoring rather than reproducing it.)\n- The \"Team\" nav button in the sidebar used to be `disabled` with `opacity: 0.5; cursor: not-allowed` and a `title=\"Team (Coming Soon)\"` tooltip — the Team feature is a demo fixture, not a real connected service. Now it's clickable and the user can reach a screen they shouldn't think is shipping.\n- More broadly: no sidebar nav button has `aria-current=\"page\"` when active; the active state is only indicated visually.\n\n### External resource\n- The Roboto Flex Google Font `<link>` was removed from the HTML head during the index.html rewrite, but the CSS still references `font-family: 'Roboto Flex', sans-serif;` in `src/style/timer.css` and `src/style/settings.css`. The font falls through to the system sans-serif, so the big timer digits and the mode-status badge render in Helvetica / Arial instead of the intended display font.\n\n## Where to look\n\nMost of this is markup work in the relevant components. To recover the prior markup verbatim, use `git show a0bb52c:src/index.html` (the pre-migration HTML that was deleted during the cutover) as a reference for each element's structure, attributes, and inline styles. Same trick works for any CSS file you need to consult.\n\nKey Leptos component locations:\n- `src/src/components/timer.rs` — stop button (around the `#play-pause-btn` and `#stop-btn` area), skip-icon variants, right-rail indicators, plus the `ICON_OPTIONS` constant around line 50 (extend from 5 emojis to 8: 3 Remix Icon options + 5 emojis; render with the appropriate `.icon-option` or `.emoji-option` class — `bridge::types::Tag` / the icon rendering branch already supports `ri-*` class detection).\n- `src/src/components/calendar.rs` — Edit Session modal (around line 532–558), the (currently missing) Tag Usage pie-chart card, and the chart-legend block under \"Today's Development\".\n- `src/src/components/history.rs` — Excel export button. Wire its click to `commands::export_sessions_xlsx(path, sessions)`.\n- `src/src/components/settings/mod.rs` — settings shell footer (the auto-save info strip + Reset to Defaults button). Reset to Defaults is `settings.set(Settings::default())`.\n- `src/src/components/settings/shortcuts.rs` — per-row Clear button + description paragraph in the `shortcut_row` view.\n- `src/src/components/auth_modal.rs` — restore the `#user-status` span in the user-dropdown header (around line 255), driven by `auth_state.with(|s| match s { Guest => \"Guest Mode\", SignedIn { .. } => \"Signed In\", _ => \"\" })`.\n- `src/src/app.rs` — sidebar nav buttons need `disabled` re-applied to Team (with `title=\"Team (Coming Soon)\"` and the muted inline style), `title=` tooltips restored where they were dropped, and an `aria-current` projection bound to the active view.\n- `src/index.html` (Trunk entry) — add `<link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto+Flex:wght@400;800&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\">` back to the `<head>`. Alternatively, vendor the Roboto Flex woff2 under `assets/fonts/` and reference via `@font-face` to avoid the external request.\n\n## Constitution / contract notes\n\n- The Calendar's restored cards (Tag Usage, chart legend) and the Focus Weekly Summary metric tiles will need data-binding work to derive their values from the session signals. If you're restoring the markup before those signals exist, leave clear `TODO` comments at each binding point so the next pass can finish them.\n- The Excel export button's click handler invokes an existing Tauri command — no new bridge surface needed.\n- The CSP in `tauri.conf.json` allows `https://fonts.googleapis.com` and `https://fonts.gstatic.com` in `style-src` and `font-src` already, so adding the font `<link>` won't trip CSP.\n- The visual-regression baselines were captured against the current (post-removal) state. Restoring elements will shift pixels. Plan to update at most 2 baselines per PR per the constitution's tolerance policy; if you need to update more, escalate explicitly.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/39/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":1},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/39/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4647","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4647/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4647/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4647/events","html_url":"https://github.com/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4647","id":4080875788,"node_id":"I_kwDOHvzHec7zPTkM","number":4647,"title":"SSR streaming hangs on 1-vCPU: Resource future never resumes","user":{"login":"oiwn","id":398035,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM5ODAzNQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/398035?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/oiwn","html_url":"https://github.com/oiwn","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oiwn/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oiwn/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oiwn/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oiwn/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oiwn/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oiwn/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oiwn/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oiwn/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oiwn/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":5365119174,"node_id":"LA_kwDOHvzHec8AAAABP8k4xg","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/labels/needs%20reproduction","name":"needs reproduction","color":"474632","default":false,"description":""}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":3,"created_at":"2026-03-16T08:03:57Z","updated_at":"2026-05-08T15:54:26Z","closed_at":"2026-05-08T15:54:26Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"**Describe the bug**\n\nOn a 1-vCPU server, SSR routes that use a Resource hang mid-stream. The browser receives the HTML shell + <Transition> fallback, then the connection stalls until timeout (ERR_INCOMPLETE_CHUNKED_ENCODING). Routes without a Resource work fine.\n\n**Leptos Dependencies**\n\n```toml\n  leptos = { version = \"0.8\", default-features = false }\n  leptos_axum = { version = \"0.8\", optional = true }\n  leptos_meta = { version = \"0.8\", default-features = false }\n  leptos_router = { version = \"0.8\", default-features = false }\n```\n\n**To Reproduce**\n\nClone the exoplanets catalog (the fix is already applied there, but you can revert worker_threads = 4 in src/main.rs to reproduce):                                                                                                      \n  \n ```\n  git clone https://github.com/oiwn/exoplanets-catalog                                                                                                                                                                                     \n  # revert worker_threads fix in src/main.rs, then:\n  docker build -f infrastructure/docker/Dockerfile -t exoplanets-local . && \\\n  docker run --cpus=1 --memory=2g \\\n    -v $(pwd)/data:/app/data \\\n    -e LEPTOS_SITE_ADDR=0.0.0.0:3000 \\\n    -p 3000:3000 \\\n    exoplanets-local\n```\n\n  Then GET `http://localhost:3000/exoplanets` - stream stalls after the fallback is sent. `/about` works fine.\n\n**Next Steps**\n\n  - I can make a PR\n  - I would like to make a PR, but need help getting started - if forcing worker_threads on single-core environments is an acceptable fix in the Leptos Axum integration or starter template, I can submit a PR\n  - This is a low priority for me and is just shared for your information\n\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4647/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4647/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"not_planned","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4672","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4672/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4672/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4672/events","html_url":"https://github.com/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4672","id":4188844247,"node_id":"I_kwDOHvzHec75rLDX","number":4672,"title":"WASM builds fail with wasm-bindgen \"failed to find N in function table\" on rustc 1.94+","user":{"login":"ksr-13","id":127506421,"node_id":"U_kgDOB5mX9Q","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/127506421?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ksr-13","html_url":"https://github.com/ksr-13","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ksr-13/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ksr-13/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ksr-13/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ksr-13/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ksr-13/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ksr-13/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ksr-13/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ksr-13/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ksr-13/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":5365119174,"node_id":"LA_kwDOHvzHec8AAAABP8k4xg","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/labels/needs%20reproduction","name":"needs reproduction","color":"474632","default":false,"description":""}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":7,"created_at":"2026-04-01T17:59:40Z","updated_at":"2026-05-08T15:54:46Z","closed_at":"2026-05-08T15:54:46Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## The Bug\n\nLeptos 0.8.x WASM builds fail when processed by wasm-bindgen CLI (0.2.115-0.2.117). The error occurs because wasm-bindgen can't find certain function table entries that the WASM file references.\n\nthread 'main' panicked at crates/cli-support/src/wit/outgoing.rs:257:61: called Result::unwrap() on an Err value: failed to find 33345 in function table\n\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Create a Leptos 0.8.x project with wasm-bindgen\n2. Build with `cargo build --target wasm32-unknown-unknown --release`\n3. Run `wasm-bindgen --target=web --out-dir=out app.wasm`\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nwasm-bindgen should successfully generate JS bindings.\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\nPanics with \"failed to find N in function table\".\n\n## Environment\n\n- **Leptos version**: 0.8.17\n- **wasm-bindgen version**: 0.2.117\n- **rustc version**: 1.94.1 (stable), nightly-2026-03-20\n- **OS**: macOS aarch64\n\n## Additional Context\n\n- This appears to be a compatibility issue between rustc 1.94's wasm codegen and wasm-bindgen's function table lookup\n- A minimal wasm-bindgen project works fine - the issue is specific to Leptos's heavy use of closures/reactive signals\n- The WASM file is ~2.2MB\n- Also filed on wasm-bindgen: https://github.com/wasm-bindgen/wasm-bindgen/issues/5076\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4672/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4672/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"not_planned","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joshuafolkken/rust-lumina/issues/1","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joshuafolkken/rust-lumina","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joshuafolkken/rust-lumina/issues/1/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joshuafolkken/rust-lumina/issues/1/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joshuafolkken/rust-lumina/issues/1/events","html_url":"https://github.com/joshuafolkken/rust-lumina/issues/1","id":4151484310,"node_id":"I_kwDORyQXZs73cp-W","number":1,"title":"create project","user":{"login":"joshuafolkken","id":168330964,"node_id":"U_kgDOCgiG1A","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/168330964?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshuafolkken","html_url":"https://github.com/joshuafolkken","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshuafolkken/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshuafolkken/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshuafolkken/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshuafolkken/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshuafolkken/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshuafolkken/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshuafolkken/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshuafolkken/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/joshuafolkken/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2026-03-27T10:45:30Z","updated_at":"2026-03-31T08:39:17Z","closed_at":"2026-03-31T08:39:17Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joshuafolkken/rust-lumina/issues/1/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joshuafolkken/rust-lumina/issues/1/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/37","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/37/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/37/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/37/events","html_url":"https://github.com/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/37","id":4416895089,"node_id":"I_kwDOSXj0Bc8AAAABB0R4cQ","number":37,"title":"Timer engine: restore event-driven side effects + fix unit/clamp/timezone errors","user":{"login":"KonstantinKo","id":779660,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc3OTY2MA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/779660?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo","html_url":"https://github.com/KonstantinKo","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":6,"created_at":"2026-05-10T21:30:16Z","updated_at":"2026-05-11T07:22:32Z","closed_at":"2026-05-11T07:22:30Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"The timer engine in `src/src/engine/timer.rs` emits `TimerEvent` variants correctly, but the consumers that turn those events into user-visible side effects are mostly missing or broken. Combined with a handful of unit-conversion / clamp / timezone errors, this is the largest behavioral-regression cluster.\n\n## User-visible symptoms\n\n### Notifications and sounds\n- Completing a 25-minute focus session no longer plays a chime or shows a system notification — the user has to be staring at the screen to know it ended.\n- No in-app toast pings on any state transition (start, pause, skip, +5, completion, etc.) — the prior version had per-action toast feedback.\n- 2-minute and 30-second remaining warnings (toast + `.warning` class on the timer container) are gone.\n\n### Smart pause\n- Smart pause never engages even with the toggle on and a real idle period. Two compounding bugs:\n  - The `smart_pause_timeout` setting is multiplied by 60 before being passed to `start_activity_monitoring`. The default 30 in settings becomes 30 *minutes* of required idle time instead of 30 seconds.\n  - Even after fixing the multiplier, nothing in the app subscribes to the `user-activity` / `user-inactivity` Tauri events that the backend emits. The engine has an `observe_activity()` API but the wire from the events into the engine is dangling.\n\n### Auto-start and continuous sessions\n- \"Auto-start sessions\" works after natural completion but not after Skip — skipping leaves the timer at the start screen.\n- \"Allow continuous sessions\" setting is connected to a flag but the engine never reads it. Focus sessions still hard-cut to break at zero-cross; the prior \"overtime\" path (negative remaining countdown, `.overtime` class, special title prefix, special tray icon) is dead.\n\n### Clamps and units\n- The `+5` button can no longer push a focus session past 25 minutes — the engine clamps at the configured mode duration. Prior version only floored at 0 (no ceiling), allowing power users to run >25-minute sessions.\n\n### Time zones\n- Session `start_time` / `end_time` shown in the calendar's session timeline are formatted from UTC, not local. A user in UTC+2 finishing a 14:00 local session sees \"12:00 – 12:25\". Same issue affects `Session.date` (used as the calendar's day-grouping key and the today-cell highlight), so sessions near midnight file under the wrong day.\n\n## Where to look\n\n- `src/src/engine/timer.rs` — the `tick` function emits `PomodoroCompleted` on the zero-cross, but `src/src/app.rs` and `src/src/components/timer.rs` don't consume it for desktop notifications or sound playback. The notification path should invoke a Tauri command (check `src/src/bridge/commands.rs` for `send_notification` or equivalent), gated on `Settings.notifications.desktop_notifications`. Sound is `web_sys::HtmlAudioElement::new_with_src(...).play()`, gated on `Settings.notifications.sound_notifications`.\n\n- `src/src/engine/timer.rs::adjust_remaining_secs` — replace the `clamp(1, max_secs)` upper bound with `max(1)`. The inline comment admits the upper clamp was an intentional choice; revert it.\n\n- `src/src/app.rs` — find where `commands::start_activity_monitoring(timeout_seconds: u64)` is called. The current call multiplies the seconds-valued `smart_pause_timeout` by 60. Drop the multiplier. Then add a `bridge::events::listen` subscription for `USER_ACTIVITY` and `USER_INACTIVITY` (constants are in `src/src/bridge/events.rs`) that calls `engine.update(|s| s.observe_activity(ActivitySignal::Active|Idle, &BrowserClock))` on each emit.\n\n- `src/src/components/timer.rs::on_skip` — should read `Settings.notifications.auto_start_timer` and call `state.start(&BrowserClock)` after the skip mutation (a 1.5s timeout for parity with the prior version is acceptable but not required).\n\n- `src/src/engine/timer.rs::tick` for the 2-min / 30-sec warning — engine knows `old_remaining` vs `new_remaining`; detect the 120→119 and 30→29 crossings and emit new `TimerEvent` variants. The consumer in `timer.rs` shows the toast + adds the `.warning` class on `.timer-container`.\n\n- `src/src/engine/timer.rs` for continuous sessions — gate the focus→break zero-cross on `!Settings.notifications.allow_continuous_sessions`. When the setting is on, enter an overtime state: negative remaining, `.overtime` class on the timer container, `+` title prefix, distinct tray icon. The prior implementation lives at `git show a0bb52c:src/core/pomodoro-timer.js` (around `770-810` and `988-1059`).\n\n- `src/src/components/timer.rs::synth_completed_session` (around line 152–170) — replace `DateTime::<Utc>::from_timestamp_millis(now_ms).format(...)` with local-time formatting. Use `js_sys::Date::new_0().get_hours()` / `get_minutes()` (gate on `target_arch = \"wasm32\"`).\n\n- `src/src/engine/date_format.rs::format_session_date` — same fix on the day-grouping key. Both producers must agree on local time.\n\n## Constitution / contract notes\n\n- The engine itself stays pure (no DOM access under `src/src/engine/`, enforced by `scripts/check-engine-purity.sh`). The side-effect wires live in the bridge and component layers.\n- Don't change `TimerEvent` variant names if existing tests depend on them; add new variants where the consumer needs them.\n- Many of these consumers depend on Settings fields that may not exist yet in the `Settings` struct. If a needed field is missing, restore it as part of that separate work.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/37/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":1},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/37/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/9","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/9/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/9/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/9/events","html_url":"https://github.com/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/9","id":4408667151,"node_id":"I_kwDOSXj0Bc8AAAABBsbsDw","number":9,"title":"Add integration tests (MockRuntime or Playwright/WebdriverIO E2E) (Phase 3)","user":{"login":"KonstantinKo","id":779660,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc3OTY2MA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/779660?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo","html_url":"https://github.com/KonstantinKo","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":5,"created_at":"2026-05-08T18:54:56Z","updated_at":"2026-05-09T13:41:57Z","closed_at":"2026-05-09T13:41:54Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Tech stack swap context (READ FIRST)\n\nThe frontend stack will be swapped soon — most likely candidate is Leptos (Rust + WASM), but not 100% decided. The whole point of investing in these tests is so the suite survives that swap and continues to validate behavior on the new stack.\n\n**Do not test implementation details.** Specifically:\n\n- Avoid mocking specific module paths or imports (`@/utils/common-utils.js`, the shape of `window.__TAURI__.invoke('plugin:foo')`, the way managers register on `window`, etc.) — those will not exist after the swap.\n- Avoid asserting on internal class/function structure (which file holds which class, which method is `private`, etc.).\n- Drive through public/user-facing behavior. For unit tests, prefer pure helpers that have stable contracts (e.g. the `helpers.rs` extraction pattern). For integration / E2E, drive the UI exactly like a real user would.\n\n**What survives the swap**: Cargo tests on pure Rust helpers, E2E tests that click and assert on visible UI state, visual regression screenshots.\n\n**What dies on the swap**: anything mocking `window.__TAURI__.invoke()` directly, anything importing from `src/managers/*.js` or `src/utils/*.js`, tests that assert \"this class is in this file\".\n\nIf a test absolutely requires implementation-detail-coupling (e.g. mocking a specific Tauri plugin invoke for a unit test), annotate it clearly with a `// TODO(stack-swap):` comment naming what would need re-doing on swap.\n\n---\n\nFollow-up to #4 — Phase 1 will be landed by that issue, this tracks Phase 3.\n\n### Phase 3 — integration tests\n\n- Tauri 2 supports `MockRuntime`; `cargo test` could then exercise the full `#[tauri::command]` surface.\n- Or set up Playwright/WebdriverIO against `tauri dev` for E2E.\n\nAcceptance: at least one integration test exercises a `#[tauri::command]` end-to-end (via `MockRuntime`) **or** an E2E suite drives `tauri dev` through a representative user flow, and the chosen runner is wired into CI.\n\n## Why `wontfix`\n\nSo Agentex's plan_and_build workflow doesn't try to land this until Phases 1 and 2 are in. Remove the label when ready to schedule.\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/9/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/9/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4610","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4610/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4610/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4610/events","html_url":"https://github.com/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4610","id":4013032655,"node_id":"I_kwDOHvzHec7vMgTP","number":4610,"title":"Intermittent panic \"callback removed before attaching\" in high-churn embedded environments (WebView2/Tauri)","user":{"login":"ordokr","id":26442816,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI2NDQyODE2","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/26442816?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ordokr","html_url":"https://github.com/ordokr","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ordokr/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ordokr/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ordokr/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ordokr/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ordokr/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ordokr/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ordokr/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ordokr/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ordokr/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":5365119174,"node_id":"LA_kwDOHvzHec8AAAABP8k4xg","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/labels/needs%20reproduction","name":"needs reproduction","color":"474632","default":false,"description":""}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":2,"created_at":"2026-03-02T19:57:02Z","updated_at":"2026-05-08T15:53:27Z","closed_at":"2026-05-08T15:53:27Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Describe the bug\nIn embedded environments like WebView2 (Tauri/Wry), rapid mounting and unmounting of DOM nodes carrying dynamic attributes or event handlers can trigger a panic: `callback removed before attaching`.\n\nThis occurs in `tachys/src/html/event.rs` (and related attribute modules) when the framework attempts to attach or dispose of a callback on a node that the host engine has already detached or dropped during a tight reactive update window. Replacing the strict `.expect()` calls with resilient fallbacks (logging an error instead of panicking) prevents the entire WASM thread from crashing.\n\n### Leptos Dependencies\n```toml\nleptos = { git = \"https://github.com/leptos-rs/leptos\", branch = \"0.9\", features = [\"csr\"] }\n```\n\n### To Reproduce\n1. Run a Leptos CSR application inside a WebView2/Tauri host.\n2. Rapidly toggle a `<Show>` boundary or navigate between views where elements have `on:click` handlers or reactive `class` tuples.\n3. Observe intermittent panics in the web console: `callback removed before attaching`.\n\n### Expected behavior\nRapid mount/unmount churn should not crash the WASM thread. At worst, event attachment/disposal should become a no-op with a diagnostic message.\n\n### Actual behavior\nIntermittent panic (crashes the WASM thread), e.g.:\n- `callback removed before attaching`\n\n### Suggested Fix\nAdopt a \"resilience-first\" approach in the Tachys renderer. Instead of panicking when a callback is missing during a race condition, the framework should log a diagnostic error and return a no-op handler, allowing the application to remain functional.\n\n### Additional context (possible related cause)\nThis same panic string is also seen when `ssr` is accidentally enabled via Cargo feature unification in a CSR app (see leptos-rs/leptos#4586 and discussion #4493). If maintainers suspect this instead of a host detach/race, I can provide a minimal workspace reproducer as well.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4610/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4610/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"not_planned","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos/issues/636","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos/issues/636/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos/issues/636/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos/issues/636/events","html_url":"https://github.com/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos/issues/636","id":4173610511,"node_id":"I_kwDOIYu7ec74xD4P","number":636,"title":"cargo-leptos 0.3.x renames `client_bg.wasm` → `client.wasm` but does not patch `client.js` to match, causing 404","user":{"login":"j055","id":6011428,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjYwMTE0Mjg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/6011428?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/j055","html_url":"https://github.com/j055","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/j055/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/j055/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/j055/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/j055/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/j055/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/j055/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/j055/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/j055/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/j055/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":2,"created_at":"2026-03-30T19:46:06Z","updated_at":"2026-03-31T17:14:28Z","closed_at":"2026-03-31T17:14:27Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Bug report\n\nRegression of #143 — the same `_bg.wasm` / 404 mismatch is present in cargo-leptos 0.3.5.\n\n### Versions\n\n| Tool | Version |\n|---|---|\n| cargo-leptos | 0.3.5 |\n| wasm-bindgen-cli | 0.2.114 |\n| leptos | 0.8.17 |\n\n### What happens\n\nAfter running `cargo leptos watch` (or `cargo leptos build`), the output in `target/site/pkg/` is:\n\n```\nclient.css\nclient.d.ts\nclient.js          ← references `client_bg.wasm` on line ~938\nclient.wasm        ← the actual WASM binary (renamed by cargo-leptos)\nclient_bg.wasm.d.ts\n```\n\n`client.js` (generated by wasm-bindgen) contains the hardcoded default:\n\n```js\nmodule_or_path = new URL('client_bg.wasm', import.meta.url);\n```\n\ncargo-leptos copies `client_bg.wasm` into the site directory **as** `client.wasm` (stripping the `_bg` suffix), but **does not patch `client.js`** to update this reference. The result is a 404 when the browser tries to load `client_bg.wasm`, which no longer exists under that name.\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\nEither:\n- cargo-leptos keeps the wasm-bindgen standard naming (`client_bg.wasm`) and serves it as-is, **or**\n- cargo-leptos renames it to `client.wasm` **and** patches the corresponding `client.js` to replace `client_bg.wasm` with `client.wasm`\n\nCurrently it does the rename but skips the JS patch.\n\n### Related\n\n- #143 (same issue, closed June 2023 without a fix being merged)\n```","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos/issues/636/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos/issues/636/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/localizethedocs/localizethedocs.github.io/issues/687","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/localizethedocs/localizethedocs.github.io","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/localizethedocs/localizethedocs.github.io/issues/687/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/localizethedocs/localizethedocs.github.io/issues/687/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/localizethedocs/localizethedocs.github.io/issues/687/events","html_url":"https://github.com/localizethedocs/localizethedocs.github.io/issues/687","id":4047474828,"node_id":"I_kwDOPMGl1M7xP5CM","number":687,"title":"[Project] leptos-book-l10n","user":{"login":"hwhsu1231","id":71438617,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcxNDM4NjE3","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/71438617?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/hwhsu1231","html_url":"https://github.com/hwhsu1231","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hwhsu1231/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hwhsu1231/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hwhsu1231/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hwhsu1231/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hwhsu1231/subscriptions","organizatio