:71438617,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcxNDM4NjE3","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/71438617?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/hwhsu1231","html_url":"https://github.com/hwhsu1231","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hwhsu1231/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hwhsu1231/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hwhsu1231/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hwhsu1231/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hwhsu1231/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hwhsu1231/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hwhsu1231/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hwhsu1231/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hwhsu1231/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"author_association":"MEMBER","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Project Request\n\n- **Project ID:** leptos-book-l10n\n- **Project Name:** Localization of The Leptos Book\n- **Project Docs Url:** https://book.leptos.dev/\n- **Project Repo Url:** https://github.com/leptos-rs/book.git\n\n\n### Generator\n\nmdBook\n\n### Checklist\n\n- [x] The Project is not requested yet.\n- [x] The Project ID is unique.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/localizethedocs/localizethedocs.github.io/issues/687/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/localizethedocs/localizethedocs.github.io/issues/687/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/38","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/38/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/38/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/38/events","html_url":"https://github.com/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/38","id":4416895989,"node_id":"I_kwDOSXj0Bc8AAAABB0R79Q","number":38,"title":"Visual: mode-aware projections + active-state class bindings never wired","user":{"login":"KonstantinKo","id":779660,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc3OTY2MA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/779660?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo","html_url":"https://github.com/KonstantinKo","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":6,"created_at":"2026-05-10T21:30:41Z","updated_at":"2026-05-11T13:03:14Z","closed_at":"2026-05-11T13:03:11Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"The codebase has CSS rules for state-aware styling (`.sidebar.break`, `.theme-option.active`, `.notification-status.status-disabled`, body backdrops per mode, etc.) but the Leptos components don't actually bind those class names to the underlying state. The stylesheets are correct; the JSX-side `class:xxx=` bindings are what's missing.\n\n## User-visible symptoms\n\n### Mode-aware theming\n- The sidebar palette stays red (focus mode) forever, even after the timer transitions to break or long-break. The timer-container in the main area correctly flips to green/blue, producing a visually jarring red-sidebar + green-main split.\n- The body background-tint per mode (focus = light pink, break = light green, longBreak = light blue) is also missing. On macOS this leaves the standard window chrome floating against a transparent body with a visible dropshadow that looks alien because the surrounding card UI no longer blends.\n- The mode-status badge above the timer reads only `\"Focus\"` / `\"Break\"` / `\"Long Break\"`. The prior version appended `\" (Paused)\"`, `\" (Auto-paused)\"`, or `\" (Overtime)\"` based on engine state — those suffixes are gone.\n\n### Settings active-state\n- In Settings → Theme, none of the three Auto / Light / Dark buttons looks \"selected\"; none of the timer-theme tiles shows the checkmark. The user has no visual signal of which theme is currently in effect.\n- In Settings → Notifications, the status panel that should be a colored frame (\"Enabled\" in green, \"Disabled\" in grey) renders as bare text plus a Test button with no padding, border, or background — looks like raw debug output.\n\n### Right-rail indicators\n- The lightbulb (smart pause), play-circle (auto-start), and repeat (continuous sessions) icons in the timer's right rail are pure decoration. Clicking them does nothing, and they never flip between `-line` and `-fill active` to reflect the underlying setting state.\n\n### Icon sizing (related root cause: DOM swap without CSS update)\n- Sidebar nav icons and timer right-rail icons render visibly smaller (~33% smaller) than before. The CSS rules `.sidebar-icon svg { width: 24px }` continue to target SVG, but the DOM now has `<i class=\"ri-...\">` (Remix Icon webfont). The `<i>` glyphs inherit default font-size (~15px), so the size rules don't match.\n\n## Where to look\n\n- `src/src/app.rs` — needs an `Effect::new` that mutates `document.body.class_name` to reflect the engine's `current_mode` (`focus` / `break` / `longBreak`), plus `class:break=move || ...` / `class:longBreak=move || ...` bindings on `<nav class=\"sidebar\">` (currently hardcoded `class=\"sidebar focus\"`). The CSS already has `.sidebar.break`, `.sidebar.longBreak`, `body.focus`, `body.break`, `body.longBreak` rules.\n\n- `src/src/components/timer.rs::mode_text` (around line 425) — extend the `Signal::derive` to read `engine.is_paused()`, `engine.is_auto_paused()`, and the overtime flag, appending the corresponding suffix to the badge.\n\n- `src/src/components/settings/theme.rs` — each theme button (Auto / Light / Dark) and each timer-theme tile needs a `class:active=move || current_theme.get() == \"<this_theme>\"` binding. The stylesheet at `src/style/settings.css` already has the `.theme-option.active` / `.timer-theme-option.active` rules. Reading the current theme requires the settings field to exist; if it doesn't, restore it as part of the related settings work.\n\n- `src/src/components/settings/notifications.rs::status_text` — currently toggles between literal `\"Enabled\"` / `\"Disabled\"` strings. Extend to also derive a modifier class name (`\"status-ready\"` when desktop_notifications=true, `\"status-disabled\"` otherwise) and bind via `class:status-ready=...` / `class:status-disabled=...`. Also restore the inline box-shape rules on `.notification-status` in `src/style/notifications.css` (padding 8px 12px, border-radius 6px, margin-top 8px, font-size 13px).\n\n- `src/src/components/timer.rs` right-rail (around line 1029–1051) — wire each indicator's `on:click` to `settings.update(|s| s.notifications.<flag> = !s.notifications.<flag>)`, plus a `class=move || if s.notifications.<flag> { \"ri-X-fill active\" } else { \"ri-X-line\" }` projection. The three flags are `smart_pause` (lightbulb), `auto_start_timer` (play-circle), and `allow_continuous_sessions` (repeat).\n\n- `src/style/sidebar.css` — the existing rules target `.sidebar-icon svg` (24px) and `.sidebar-icon-large svg` (26px). Either rewrite the selectors to target `i` (and use `font-size` instead of `width`/`height`), or add equivalent rules for `i`. Same issue applies to other CSS that targets SVG children of icon containers; sweep the stylesheets for `svg` selectors that may now be targeting nothing.\n\n## Constitution / contract notes\n\n- The visual-regression baselines under `tests/e2e/__screenshots__/visual-regression/` were captured against the current (incomplete) state, so they don't catch any of this. Updating bindings may shift pixels — check that the suite still passes within the 2% tolerance in `playwright.config.js`. If a baseline genuinely needs updating, do so with one-line PR justification per the constitution's tolerance policy. Re-capturing more than 2 baselines requires escalation.\n\n- The right-rail indicator wiring depends on `Settings.notifications` flags being persisted correctly. If the settings field doesn't write back to disk, restore that as part of the settings work first.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/38/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":1},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/38/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/noshishiRust/leptos-daisyui-rs/issues/19","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/noshishiRust/leptos-daisyui-rs","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/noshishiRust/leptos-daisyui-rs/issues/19/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/noshishiRust/leptos-daisyui-rs/issues/19/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/noshishiRust/leptos-daisyui-rs/issues/19/events","html_url":"https://github.com/noshishiRust/leptos-daisyui-rs/issues/19","id":3940698913,"node_id":"I_kwDOPDmA0M7q4ksh","number":19,"title":"Resolve markdown path deterministically and track file changes using a stable approach.","user":{"login":"noshishiRust","id":155700115,"node_id":"U_kgDOCUfLkw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/155700115?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/noshishiRust","html_url":"https://github.com/noshishiRust","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noshishiRust/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noshishiRust/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noshishiRust/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noshishiRust/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noshishiRust/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noshishiRust/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noshishiRust/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noshishiRust/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noshishiRust/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-02-14T07:42:01Z","updated_at":"2026-05-17T02:54:54Z","closed_at":"2026-05-17T02:54:54Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟠 Major_\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n<summary>🧩 Analysis chain</summary>\r\n\r\n🏁 Script executed:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\n# First, find the file and check its content around the specified lines\r\ncat -n demo-macros/src/lib.rs | sed -n '100,120p'\r\n```\r\n\r\nRepository: noshishiRust/leptos-daisyui-rs\r\n\r\nLength of output: 1363\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n🏁 Script executed:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\n# Check the MSRV in the Cargo.toml files\r\nfind . -name \"Cargo.toml\" -type f | head -5\r\n```\r\n\r\nRepository: noshishiRust/leptos-daisyui-rs\r\n\r\nLength of output: 129\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n🏁 Script executed:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\n# Check MSRV in Cargo.toml files\r\ncat -n ./Cargo.toml | grep -A 2 -B 2 \"rust-version\\|edition\"\r\necho \"---\"\r\ncat -n ./demo-macros/Cargo.toml | grep -A 2 -B 2 \"rust-version\\|edition\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nRepository: noshishiRust/leptos-daisyui-rs\r\n\r\nLength of output: 359\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n🏁 Script executed:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\n# Check when proc_macro::tracked_path was stabilized\r\nweb_search \"proc_macro::tracked_path stabilization MSRV Rust version\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nRepository: noshishiRust/leptos-daisyui-rs\r\n\r\nLength of output: 124\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n🌐 Web query:\r\n\r\n`proc_macro::tracked_path stabilization Rust MSRV requirements`\r\n\r\n💡 Result:\r\n\r\n### Stabilization status\r\n\r\n`proc_macro::tracked_path` (specifically `proc_macro::tracked_path::path`) is **not stabilized** as of the latest stable Rust docs; it is documented as a **nightly-only experimental API** under the feature gate **`track_path`** (tracking issue **#99515**). [1]\r\n\r\nThe corresponding environment-variable API `proc_macro::tracked_env::var` is also **nightly-only experimental** (feature gate `proc_macro_tracked_env`, same tracking issue). [2][3]\r\n\r\n### MSRV / toolchain requirements\r\n\r\n- **Stable Rust MSRV:** *None* (you **cannot** use `proc_macro::tracked_path` on stable at any version while it remains unstable). [1]  \r\n- **Nightly requirement:** You need a **nightly toolchain** where the API exists, and your proc-macro crate must enable the feature gate:\r\n  - `#![feature(track_path)]` to use `proc_macro::tracked_path::path` [3]\r\n  - (optionally) `#![feature(proc_macro_tracked_env)]` to use `proc_macro::tracked_env::var` [3]\r\n\r\n### Practical notes / alternatives (when you must support stable)\r\n\r\n- If your proc-macro reads files and you need rebuilds-on-change **on stable**, you generally have to use a workaround such as:\r\n  - moving the file IO to `build.rs` and emitting `cargo:rerun-if-changed=...`, or\r\n  - expanding to stable constructs that cause Cargo/rustc to track inputs (e.g., `include_str!` / `include_bytes!` at the call site), depending on your design.\r\n- Some crates explicitly treat `track_path` as “nightly-only” and require nightly to test it (example: `sqlx` docs mention enabling the `track_path` feature requires nightly). [4]\r\n\r\n**Sources:**  \r\n[1] Rust docs: `proc_macro::tracked_path` is nightly-only experimental (`track_path` `#99515`)  \r\n[2] Rust docs: `proc_macro::tracked_env` is nightly-only experimental (`proc_macro_tracked_env` `#99515`)  \r\n[3] `proc_macro` source showing `#[unstable(feature = \"track_path\" / \"proc_macro_tracked_env\", issue = \"99515\")]`  \r\n[4] `sqlx_build_trust` docs describing `track_path` as a nightly-only capability\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n🏁 Script executed:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\n# Also check the full Cargo.toml for demo-macros to see if there's an explicit rust-version\r\ncat demo-macros/Cargo.toml\r\n```\r\n\r\nRepository: noshishiRust/leptos-daisyui-rs\r\n\r\nLength of output: 281\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n🏁 Script executed:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\n# Check if there are any nightly feature gates in the proc-macro crate\r\nhead -20 demo-macros/src/lib.rs | grep -E \"^#!\\[feature\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nRepository: noshishiRust/leptos-daisyui-rs\r\n\r\nLength of output: 56\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n🏁 Script executed:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\n# Check the parent Cargo.toml to see if there's a global MSRV or if nightly is required\r\ncat Cargo.toml\r\n```\r\n\r\nRepository: noshishiRust/leptos-daisyui-rs\r\n\r\nLength of output: 390\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</details>\r\n\r\n**Resolve markdown path deterministically and track file changes using a stable approach.**\r\n\r\nThe hardcoded relative path depends on the compiler's CWD and the macro doesn't track markdown files as inputs, so doc edits may not trigger rebuilds. Additionally, `expect` panics instead of emitting a compile-time error with span context.\r\n\r\nFor stable Rust, use `CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR` to anchor the path and move file I/O to `build.rs` with `cargo:rerun-if-changed` to ensure incremental rebuild correctness. Alternatively, if your MSRV permits nightly, `proc_macro::tracked_path::path` requires the unstable `track_path` feature gate.\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n<summary>✅ Suggested fix (stable approach: CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR + improved error handling)</summary>\r\n\r\n```diff\r\n-use std::fs::read_to_string;\r\n+use std::fs::read_to_string;\r\n+use std::path::PathBuf;\r\n\r\n     // **TODO**: Make this path configurable. Currently hardcoded relative path assumes\r\n     // specific crate structure. Should use environment variables or macro attributes.\r\n-    let file = format!(\"../doc/components/{component}.md\");\r\n+    let manifest_dir = std::env::var(\"CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR\")\r\n+        .expect(\"CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR not set\");\r\n+    let file = PathBuf::from(manifest_dir)\r\n+        .join(\"../doc/components\")\r\n+        .join(format!(\"{component}.md\"));\r\n\r\n     // **TODO**: Add proper error handling with custom error types and useful messages.\r\n     // Currently panics with generic message if file not found.\r\n-    let markdown = read_to_string(file).expect(\"Failed to read component documentation file\");\r\n+    let markdown = match read_to_string(&file) {\r\n+        Ok(m) => m,\r\n+        Err(e) => {\r\n+            return syn::Error::new_spanned(\r\n+                &input,\r\n+                format!(\"Failed to read markdown file {}: {e}\", file.display()),\r\n+            )\r\n+            .to_compile_error()\r\n+            .into();\r\n+        }\r\n+    };\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen add to your `build.rs` (or create one):\r\n```rust\r\nfn main() {\r\n    // Emit rebuild directive for all markdown files in doc/components/\r\n    println!(\"cargo:rerun-if-changed=doc/components\");\r\n}\r\n```\r\n</details>\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n<summary>🤖 Prompt for AI Agents</summary>\r\n\r\n```\r\nIn `@demo-macros/src/lib.rs` around lines 106 - 113, Replace the hardcoded\r\nrelative path and panicking read with a deterministic, build-time driven\r\napproach: construct the path using CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR (use the existing file\r\nvariable/path logic to refer to the component file) and move the file read out\r\nof the proc-macro into build.rs so you can emit a cargo:rerun-if-changed for\r\ndoc/components (ensuring rebuilds on edits); in build.rs read or validate the\r\nmarkdown files and surface any errors as compile errors with clear messages\r\n(rather than using read_to_string(...).expect(...)) so the proc-macro\r\n(referencing the markdown variable) receives validated content or a clear\r\ncompile-time error.\r\n```\r\n\r\n</details>\r\n\r\n<!-- fingerprinting:phantom:medusa:eagle -->\r\n\r\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment by CodeRabbit -->\r\n\r\n_Originally posted by @coderabbitai[bot] in https://github.com/noshishiRust/leptos-daisyui-rs/pull/17#discussion_r2807147003_\r\n            ","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/noshishiRust/leptos-daisyui-rs/issues/19/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/noshishiRust/leptos-daisyui-rs/issues/19/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/36","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/36/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/36/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/36/events","html_url":"https://github.com/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/36","id":4416893835,"node_id":"I_kwDOSXj0Bc8AAAABB0Rziw","number":36,"title":"Settings: complete the data-model and the read/write wires across the app","user":{"login":"KonstantinKo","id":779660,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc3OTY2MA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/779660?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo","html_url":"https://github.com/KonstantinKo","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/KonstantinKo/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":6,"created_at":"2026-05-10T21:29:43Z","updated_at":"2026-05-10T22:45:36Z","closed_at":"2026-05-10T22:45:33Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"Multiple post-migration settings are non-persistent or non-functional because the underlying `Settings` / `AppSettings` struct is missing fields, or the UI handlers don't read/write them, or no consumer reads them after they're set.\n\n## User-visible symptoms\n\n- Theme picker doesn't survive a restart — pick Dark → relaunch → app is back to its default.\n- The app no longer follows the OS dark-mode preference on first launch.\n- \"Allow continuous sessions\" toggle in Notifications settings does nothing — focus sessions still hard-cut to break at zero-cross instead of entering overtime.\n- \"Max Session Time\" input in General settings is hardcoded `value=\"120\"` — typing a new number is silently discarded, and the 2-hour auto-pause cap that catches forgotten timers no longer enforces at all.\n- \"Skip release\" on the update banner only closes for this session; the skipped version reappears on next launch.\n- \"Continue as Guest\" on the auth modal works in-session, but on next launch the user is back at \"Unauthenticated\" and must dismiss the modal again.\n- The Calendar's Focus Weekly Summary card permanently shows \"0m\" / \"0m\" / \"0\" / \"0m\" regardless of completed sessions.\n- The progress dot row above the timer always shows at least 11 dots — set \"Total Sessions\" to 5 in Settings and the row still shows 11.\n\n## Where to look\n\n- `src/src/bridge/types.rs` — the `Settings`, `TimerSettings`, `NotificationSettings`, `AdvancedSettings` structs. Missing fields include an `appearance` block (`theme`, `timer_theme`), `timer.max_session_time` (minutes), and full plumbing for `skipped_versions` / `guest_mode` / `auth_seen` (these may exist as fields but have no readers/writers).\n- `src-tauri/src/lib.rs` — the `AppSettings` struct mirrors the Leptos side and must change in lockstep. `default_*()` helpers must round-trip with the new fields. Use `#[serde(default)]` on new fields for backward-compat with existing on-disk files.\n- `src/src/components/settings/{theme,general,notifications,advanced}.rs` — each input needs an `on:change` that mutates the shared `RwSignal<Settings>`. A debounced persistence sink in `src/src/app.rs` already writes any signal mutation through to disk; you should not need to introduce a new save flow.\n- `src/src/components/auth_modal.rs` — the `on:click` for `#continue-guest` calls `auth_state.set(AuthState::Guest)` directly. It should go through `AuthManager::continue_as_guest` in `src/src/managers/auth.rs`, which already knows how to persist the guest flag via the `GuestModeStore`.\n- `src/src/components/update_notification.rs` — the \"Skip release\" button's `on:close` should mutate `settings.skipped_versions` (push current version, dedupe). The `UPDATE_AVAILABLE` event listener should filter against that list before lifting `UpdateInfo::Available`.\n- `src/src/components/calendar.rs` — the \"Focus Weekly Summary\" tiles (around line 307–343) have static `\"0m\"` / `\"0\"` literals. Replace with `Signal::derive` projections off `use_context::<RwSignal<Vec<ManualSession>>>()`.\n- `src/src/components/timer.rs` — the progress dots count line reads `settings.with(|s| s.timer.total_sessions.max(11))`. The `.max(11)` clamp is wrong; should be the raw setting value (with a sane non-zero floor of 1). The adjacent comment says \"JS-era default was 11\" — that's incorrect, the prior default was 10.\n- `src/src/components/settings/theme.rs` — `on_theme` / `on_timer_theme` currently only call `set_html_attr(\"data-theme\", ...)`. They should also mutate the new `Settings.appearance.theme` field. The legacy migration reader (`LegacySettingsPayload` in `src/src/bridge/types.rs`) already deserializes a `theme_preference` from on-disk JSON but the import handler drops it — fold it into the new `appearance` field.\n- `src/src/app.rs` — needs a cold-start effect that calls `theme::loader::apply_theme(resolve_color_mode(settings.appearance.theme, system_prefers_dark()))` after settings load resolves, so the OS dark-mode preference is honored on first launch and the persisted choice is restored on subsequent launches.\n\n## Suggested approach\n\n1. Widen `Settings` (Leptos) and `AppSettings` (Tauri) in lockstep with the missing fields.\n2. Wire every settings input's `on:change` to the shared signal.\n3. Wire the cold-start `apply_theme` effect.\n4. Have downstream consumers (engine for `allow_continuous_sessions` / `max_session_time`; update-notification listener for `skipped_versions`; calendar tiles for derived metrics) read the new fields.\n\nThe engine-side enforcement of `max_session_time` and `allow_continuous_sessions` is its own work — settle the data shape and reads here first.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/36/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":1},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/KonstantinKo/presto/issues/36/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos/issues/470","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos/issues/470/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos/issues/470/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos/issues/470/events","html_url":"https://github.com/leptos-rs/cargo-leptos/issues/470","id":2938718856,"node_id":"I_kwDOIYu7ec6vKUqI","number":470,"title":"openssl-sys dependency breaks windows install on 0.2.30 and above","user":{"login":"Hecatron","id":8965579,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg5NjU1Nzk=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/8965579?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Hecatron","html_url":"https://github.com/Hecatron","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Hecatron/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Hecatron/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Hecatron/gists{/