n2024","id":153411856,"node_id":"U_kgDOCSThEA","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/153411856?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Bohemian2024","html_url":"https://github.com/Bohemian2024","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Bohemian2024/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Bohemian2024/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Bohemian2024/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Bohemian2024/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Bohemian2024/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Bohemian2024/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Bohemian2024/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Bohemian2024/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Bohemian2024/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2026-04-01T08:29:59Z","updated_at":"2026-04-01T12:09:11Z","closed_at":"2026-04-01T12:09:11Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"**Describe the bug**\nview! macro can't support explicit type annotation in closure\n\n**Leptos Dependencies**\n\nPlease copy and paste the Leptos dependencies and features from your `Cargo.toml`.\n\nFor example:\n```toml\nconsole_error_panic_hook = \"0.1.7\"\nleptos = { version = \"0.8.17\", features = [\"csr\"] }\n```\n\n**To Reproduce**\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\n1. I follow the guide from https://book.leptos.dev/view/04_iteration.html\n2. and write down the following code, running \"trunk serve --open\" in terminal will return the following error.\nerror: expected identifier, found keyword `move`\n  --> src/main.rs:43:26\n   |\n43 |                 children=move |index: ReadSignal<usize>, counter: Counter| {\n   |                          ^^^^ expected identifier, found keyword\n   |\nhelp: escape `move` to use it as an identifier\n   |\n43 |                 children=r#move |index: ReadSignal<usize>, counter: Counter| {\n   |                          ++\n\nerror: expected one of `async`, `|`, or `||`, found `}`\n\nMy understanding:\n  When the view! macro parses the children attribute, it sees children=.... It then expects a valid value. The issue arises with the colon (:) in the type annotations.\n\n  The `view!` macro's internal parser interprets the colon (`:`) as part of a different syntax (like `class:name=...`), not as part of a type annotation within a closure.\n\n**Screenshots**\n\n<img width=\"1372\" height=\"623\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3e6899ac-c811-4ca4-b486-1061bca5da1e\" />\n\n\nThe only solution so far is removing type annotation in closure, but type annotation should be correct from Rust point of view. In the end, it looks a bug inside rsx! implementation. Please double check, thanks!\n\n<img width=\"950\" height=\"190\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2e62720f-2e1e-4621-a2bc-46f0dc1f6114\" />","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4669/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4669/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/3060","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/3060/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/3060/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/3060/events","html_url":"https://github.com/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/3060","id":2561464586,"node_id":"I_kwDOHvzHec6YrNkK","number":3060,"title":"Document the \"multiple classes for one condition\" syntax (and implement it in 0.7)","user":{"login":"gbj","id":286622,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI4NjYyMg==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/286622?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/gbj","html_url":"https://github.com/gbj","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gbj/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gbj/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gbj/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gbj/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gbj/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gbj/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gbj/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gbj/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gbj/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":4381648746,"node_id":"LA_kwDOHvzHec8AAAABBSqnag","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/labels/documentation","name":"documentation","color":"FDE77D","default":true,"description":"Improvements or additions to documentation"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":2,"created_at":"2024-10-02T12:19:06Z","updated_at":"2026-05-06T17:47:28Z","closed_at":"2026-05-06T17:47:27Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"The syntax discussed in https://github.com/leptos-rs/leptos/discussio