te":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":4,"created_at":"2026-01-22T22:52:18Z","updated_at":"2026-05-13T15:17:42Z","closed_at":"2026-05-13T15:17:42Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"_I'm following the bug report template for discoverability, but please note that I also created a minimum reproducible example repository here: https://github.com/tannerntannern/leptos-firefox-bug-reprex_\n\n**Describe the bug**\n\n`<Suspense>` within `<details>` element causes panic only in release mode, and only on Firefox (latest version).  The `<details>` element might not be the root cause, but it's unclear to me what is.\n\n**Code snippets**\n\n<details>\n<summary>Dependencies</summary>\n\n```toml\n# common\nleptos = { version = \"0.8.15\", features = [\"tracing\"] }\n\n# frontend only\nconsole_error_panic_hook = { version = \"0.1.7\", optional = true }\nwasm-bindgen = { version = \"=0.2.106\", optional = true }\n\n# backend only\naxum = { version = \"0.8.8\", optional = true }\nleptos_axum = { version = \"0.8.7\", features = [\"tracing\"], optional = true }\ntokio = { version = \"1\", features = [\"full\"], optional = true }\n```\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>App component</summary>\n\n```rs\n#[component]\npub fn App() -> impl IntoView {\n    let data_resource = OnceResource::new(get_data());\n    view! {\n        <details open>\n            <summary>\"Server Data\"</summary>\n            <Suspense fallback=move || view! { <div>\"Loading data\"</div> }>\n                {move || Suspend::new(async move {\n                    let data = data_resource.await.unwrap();\n                    view! {\n                        \"Data: \"{data}\n                    }\n                })}\n            </Suspense>\n        </details>\n    }\n}\n\n#[server]\nasync fn get_data() -> Result<String, ServerFnError> {\n    Ok(\"abc123\".to_string())\n}\n```\n\n</details>\n\n**To Reproduce**\n\n1. Install cargo-leptos version `0.3.2`\n1. Run `cargo leptos watch --release` (could not reproduce in debug mode)\n1. Open the app in Firefox for MacOS (tested on latest version; could not reproduce in Chrome or Safari)\n1. Observe following error in the console (behavior is not consistent, might need to refresh a few times)\n\n**Error details**\n\nYou should see something to the effect of\n```\npanicked at /Users/tnielsen/.cargo/registry/src/index.crates.io-1949cf8c6b5b557f/tachys-0.2.11/src/hydration.rs:227:9:\ninternal error: entered unreachable code\n...\n```\n\n**Screenshots**\n\n<img width=\"1086\" height=\"581\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/15c34ef2-89d0-49e1-b4b7-36f4c636b803\" />\n\n**Next Steps**\n\n- [ ] I will make a PR\n- [X] I would like to make a PR, but need help getting started\n- [X] I want someone else to take the time to fix this\n- [ ] This is a low priority for me and is just shared for your information\n\n**Additional context**\n\nI can make any of the following changes in `app.rs` and the error goes away:\n- Change the `<details>` element to a `<div>`\n- Remove the outer `<details>` element entirely\n- Change the `Suspense` fallback to `move || \"Loading data\"` (from `move || view! { <div>\"Loading data\"</div> }`)\n\nAlso mentioned above, but I cannot reproduce in any browser except Firefox.  I can only reproduce in release mode.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4546/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-rs/leptos/issues/4546/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/leptos-